{"search_data": "Central ARIIA 2019 Online Application \u2013 Atal Ranking of Institutions on Innovation Achievements Central govt. is inviting Atal Ranking of Institutions on Innovation Achievements online application forms at ariia.gov.in to promote culture of innovation in higher education institutions, check eligibility, indicators, parameters & weightage before filling ARIIA 2019 online registration formTable of Contents  ARIIA 2019 Online Application Form at ariia.gov.inARIIA Ranking 2019 ParamtersReferencesARIIA 2019 Online Application Form at ariia.gov.inBelow is the complete procedure to apply online for Atal Ranking of Institutions on Innovation Achievements 2019:-Visit the official website ariia.gov.inAt the homepage, click at the \u201cApply for ARIIA 2019\u201d tab to open the ARIIA 2019 registration form as shown below:-ARIIA 2019 Online Registration FormHere all the educational institutions will have to select their state, college / university name, enter e-mail ID and click at the \u201cSend registration details\u201d to complete the registration process.Afterwards, institutions will be directed to the ARIIA 2019 login page as shown below:-Atal Ranking of Institutions on Innovation Achievements LoginInstitutions needs to enter the username and password sent on their registered e-mail ID to continue to fill the ARIIA 2019 online application form which will appear as shown below:-ARIIA 2019 Online Application FormFinally, institutions can fill the institute details, details of nodal officer and head of institution and then click at the \u201cSubmit\u201d button to complete the application process.ARIIA rankings 2019 will inspire Indian institutions to reorient their mind-set and build ecosystems to encourage high quality research, innovation and entrepreneurship.ARIIA Ranking 2019 ParamtersThe ARIIA rankings 2019 will be primarily based on the 5 main parameters which are described below:-IndicatorsWeightageBudget expenses and revenue generated through innovation and entrepreneurship development20Facilitating access to advance centers and entrepreneurial support system10Ideal to entrepreneurship54Development of innovation ecosystems supported through teaching & learning10Best innovative solutions developed In-house to improve governance of your institutions6Total100The overall score can take a maximum value of 100 and the institutions will be rank-ordered based on their scores.Big opportunity for HE Institutions in India to participate in #ARIIA (Atal Ranking of Institutions on Innovation Achievements), an initiate of @HRDMinistry to rank all major HE Institutions on \u201cInnovation & Entrepreneurship Development\u201d. Registration started & closes on Nov 15. pic.twitter.com/wJ9AZxWZOO\u2014 Prakash Javadekar (@PrakashJavdekar) October 29, 2018ARIIA 2019 is going to focus on quality of innovations and will also measure the real impact created by these innovations nationally and internationally.References\u2014 To see the complete features, eligibility criteria, indicators and other details, click at the link \u2013 https://www.facilities.aicte-india.org/IC/ARIIA%20Booklet.pdf \u2014 In case of any query, institutions can call on the help on the helpline number 011-29581235, 1226 or can send an e-mail to contact-ariia@gov.in (Mon to Fri 10 a.m to 6 p.m) \u2014 For more details, visit the official website http://www.ariia.gov.in/  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}